spanishExample: Siempre desayuno leyendo, me gusta mucho.
englishTranslation: I always have breakfast reading; I like it a lot.

spanishExample: No sé si viaja en febrero o junio, deberías preguntarle.
englishTranslation: I don't know if he travels in February or June, you should ask him.

spanishExample: Los sábados salimos a cenar.
englishTranslation: On Saturdays we go out to dinner.

spanishExample: Debí haberte dicho eso en marzo.
englishTranslation: I should(Deber preterite) have told you that in March.

spanishExample: Lo supe a través de ellos por eso viajé en septiembre.
englishTranslation: I found out via them that’s why I traveled in September.

spanishExample: Ella desayunó en casa, pero cenó afuera.
englishTranslation: She had breakfast at home, but had dinner out.

spanishExample: Él desayuna mientras escribe sus historias.
englishTranslation: He has breakfast while he writes his stories.

spanishExample: Debería haberse probado eso, pero creo que le va a quedar bien.
englishTranslation: She should have tried that on, but I think it’s going to suit her well.

spanishExample: Ellos cenan a las nueve, pero yo ceno más tarde.
englishTranslation: They have dinner at nine, but I have dinner later.

spanishExample: Leí que tendrás problemas si viajas a esos lugares en enero.
englishTranslation: I read(past) that you’ll have problems if you travel to those places in January.

spanishExample: Siempre almorzamos en casa, pero hoy almorcé afuera.
englishTranslation: We always have lunch at home, but today I had lunch out.

spanishExample: No he aprendido nada.
englishTranslation: I haven’t learned anything.

spanishExample: Debería haberme ido más temprano.
englishTranslation: I should(Deber conditional) have left earlier.

spanishExample: Lee lo que dice ahí antes de que salgamos a desayunar.
englishTranslation: Read what it says there before we go out for breakfast.

spanishExample: Podríamos habernos quedado más tiempo porque aprendí eso viajando.
englishTranslation: We could have stayed longer because I learned that traveling.

spanishExample: Ellos almorzaron en casa, pero a la noche cenamos solos.
englishTranslation: They had lunch at home, but at night we had dinner alone.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué cenas tan tarde si ella cena temprano?
englishTranslation: Why do you eat dinner so late if she has dinner early?

spanishExample: Leo lo que ellos habían escrito el jueves.
englishTranslation: I’m reading what they had written on Thursday.

spanishExample: Viajaron ahí el año pasado y quieren escribir un libro.
englishTranslation: They traveled there last year and they want to write a book.

spanishExample: Desayuné con ellos y estuvimos juntos un rato.
englishTranslation: I had breakfast with them and we were together for a little while.

spanishExample: Ya aprendiste que diciembre es el peor mes para eso.
englishTranslation: You already learned that December is the worst month for that.

spanishExample: Cenamos ahí durante el verano, pero en otoño nos quedamos aquí.
englishTranslation: We have dinner there during the Summer, but in the Fall we stay here.

spanishExample: ¿Por qué almuerzas a esa hora? Debes aprender a hacerlo antes.
englishTranslation: Why do you have lunch at that time? You must learn to do it earlier.

spanishExample: ¿A qué hora almorzaste? ¿Y cenaste en casa?
englishTranslation: At what time did you have lunch? And did you have dinner at home?

spanishExample: Viajamos ahí en abril, pero he leído que es mejor en mayo.
englishTranslation: We travel there in April, but I've read that it’s better in May.

spanishExample: Tengo que leer lo que ella escribió en noviembre.
englishTranslation: I have to read what she wrote in November.

spanishExample: Me gustaría haberla visto durante la primavera.
englishTranslation: I would like to have seen her during the Spring.

spanishExample: Estaba escribiendo una historia.
englishTranslation: She was writing a story.

spanishExample: Quieren que yo viaje a donde él viajó el año pasado.
englishTranslation: They want me to travel to where he traveled last year.

spanishExample: Podría haberle dicho eso en julio, pero se lo diré el miércoles.
englishTranslation: I could have told her that in July, but I’ll tell it to her on Wednesday.

spanishExample: En octubre viajaste a donde ellos siempre viajan.
englishTranslation: In October you traveled to where they always travel.

spanishExample: Han estado viajando, pero el viernes podemos almorzar con ellos.
englishTranslation: They’ve been traveling, but on Friday we can have lunch with them.

spanishExample: Ellos almuerzan muy temprano, pero ella almuerza como a las dos.
englishTranslation: They have lunch very early, but she has lunch like at two.

spanishExample: Aprende eso y no tendrás problemas el martes.
englishTranslation: Learn that and you won’t have problems on Tuesday.

spanishExample: Cuando viajo, almuerzo a cualquier hora.
englishTranslation: When I travel, I have lunch at any time.

spanishExample: Quiero que viaje en agosto para que lea lo que escribí.
englishTranslation: I want him to travel in August so that he reads what I wrote.

spanishExample: Creo que quiero viajar en verano.
englishTranslation: I think I want to travel in Summer.

spanishExample: Tú siempre desayunas lo que ellos desayunan.
englishTranslation: You always eat for breakfast what they have for breakfast.

spanishExample: Lee el principio de ese libro y aprende mucho.
englishTranslation: He’s reading the beginning of that book and he’s learning a lot.

spanishExample: No tengo una estación favorita.
englishTranslation: I don’t have a favorite season.

spanishExample: Me gustaría haberlo visto antes de la boda.
englishTranslation: I would like to have seen him before the wedding.

spanishExample: Escribe lo que piensas y todo estará bien.
englishTranslation: Write what you think and everything will be fine.

spanishExample: Siempre desayunamos en casa, pero hoy desayunamos en otro lugar.
englishTranslation: We always have breakfast at home, but today we had breakfast at another place.
